%% Diagram: Optimistic update lifecycle (TanStack Query useMutation)
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant U as User
    participant C as Component
    participant QC as Query Cache
    participant S as Server

    U->>C: Submit edit
    C->>QC: cancelQueries(['todos'])
    C->>QC: snapshot = getQueryData(['todos'])
    C->>QC: setQueryData(['todos'], optimistic)
    Note over C,QC: UI re-renders instantly with optimistic value
    C->>S: mutationFn(payload)
    alt Server accepts
        S-->>C: 200 + canonical row
        C->>QC: invalidateQueries(['todos']) on settle
        QC->>S: background refetch
        S-->>QC: authoritative data
    else Server rejects
        S-->>C: 4xx / 5xx / network
        C->>QC: setQueryData(['todos'], snapshot)
        Note over C,QC: Roll back to pre-mutation state
    end
